{
  "texts": [
    "For example, the BRIO summary in Figure 2 for one of the fiction mentions 'the German writer and photographer Barbara Hepworth' even though it has not been appeared in the source document.",
    "We also tested whether providing salient enti-8 Although fiction is considered a written genre, the data contains substantial dialogue between characters.",
    "ties to the model would improve performance.",
    "Table 3 shows CTRLSum and GPT scores in three settings: adding gold salient entities that have the top 3 frequent mentions in the document (GOLD), adding predicted salient entities from the GPT-4 model (PRED), and no salient entities provided (ZERO).",
    "Unsurprisingly, GPT with gold salient entities (GPTGold) outperforms all models, with F 1 = 0.594."
  ]
}